    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the submission on the basis that all five operating points demonstrated predicted NIH values below the absolute clinical threshold, and the Monte Carlo 95th-percentile bound encompassed the experimental mean. Although multiple credibility factors remain below required levels and several are not-assessed, the regulatory submission path allows conditional acceptance with documented gaps and a post-market surveillance commitment. The primary hemolysis validation result was considered sufficient given the detailed narrative description of the experimental campaign and CFD post-processing methodology. The absence of a structured provenance link on the primary validation result was not flagged during review, as the prose description was judged to provide adequate traceability.",
